The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Another Bihar MLA gets life
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     Another Bihar MLA gets life
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                          Sunil Pandey. Picture by Deepak Kumar                                  
	Patna, Sept. 17: A court today sentenced a JD(U) legislator, Sunil Pandey, and four others to life imprisonment in connection with the kidnapping of a Patna-based doctor in 2003.        
	The Patna district and sessions court also imposed a fine of Rs 50,000 each on the convicted persons. There were nine accused in the case originally, but four persons are still at large.        
	Sunil Pandey is the fourth elected peoples representative in the state to have been convicted for life in a criminal case. Others who have been convicted in the past two years include, RJDs Siwan MP Mohammed Shahabuddin, RJD Madhepura MP Pappu Yadav and LJP MP from Balia Surajbaan Singh.                                                                                                                                                                         
